posts.title: MAGAthread: President Trump to Hold a Rally in Wilkes-Barre, PA @ 4:00 PM Trump/Eastern time
posts.content:
President Trump is back in the Keystone state, this time hosting a rally in Wilkes-Barre. The city and surrounding area have long been supporters of President Trump and on November 5th will vote to Make America Great Again!

Cities like Wilkes-Barre represent the hard work and determination that made our country great. Wilkes-Barre fueled "Made in America", enabling us to build bridges, buildings, and futures right here in America.

Here's some trivia about Wilkes-Barre and it's contributions to America:

  • Founded in 1769 by Major John Durkee and named after British politicians John Wilkes and Isaac Barré, who were supporters of the American colonies.

  • Nicknamed "The Diamond City” due to its coal mining history. Anthracite coal, was commonly referred to as "black diamonds"

  • Played a crucial role in America's Industrial Revolution due to its rich coal deposits, which fueled the growth of the city and U.S. steel industry.

  • Located along the Susquehanna River, which played an important role in its development and means of transportation and power.

President Trump is estimated to take the stage at 4:00 PM Trump/Eastern time.

Here are some options to stream today's rally:

RSBN YouTube

RSBN Rumble

Newsmax YouTube

posts.title: MAGAthread: President Trump to Hold a Rally in Wilkes-Barre, PA @ 4:00 PM Trump/Eastern time
posts.content:
President Trump is back in the Keystone state, this time hosting a rally in Wilkes-Barre. The city and surrounding area have long been supporters of President Trump and on November 5th will vote to Make America Great Again!

Cities like Wilkes-Barre represent the hard work and determination that made our country great. Wilkes-Barre fueled "Made in America", enabling us to build bridges, buildings, and futures right here in America.

Here's some trivia about Wilkes-Barre and it's contributions to America:

  • Founded in 1769 by Major John Durkee and named after British politicians John Wilkes and Isaac Barré, who were supporters of the American colonies.

  • Nicknamed "The Diamond City” due to its coal mining history. Anthracite coal, was commonly referred to as "black diamonds"

  • Played a crucial role in America's Industrial Revolution due to its rich coal deposits, which fueled the growth of the city and U.S. steel industry.

  • Located along the Susquehanna River, which played an important role in its development and means of transportation and power.

President Trump is estimated to take the stage at 4:00 PM Trump/Eastern time.

Here are some options to stream today's rally:

RSBN YouTube

RSBN Rumble

Newsmax YouTube

- Played a crucial role in America's Industrial Revolution due to its rich coal deposits, which fueled the growth of the city and U.S. steel industry.

- Located along the Susquehanna River, which played an important role in its development and means of transportation and power.
